Marcus aurelius
Reject your sense of injury and the injury itself disappears
On the power of the mind: "You have power over your mind – not outside events. Realize this, and you will find strength."
On the value of life: "When you arise in the morning, think of what a precious privilege it is to be alive – to breathe, to think, to enjoy, to love."   
On the nature of reality: "Everything we hear is an opinion, not a fact. Everything we see is a perspective, not the truth."
On the importance of self-control: "The happiness of your life depends upon the quality of your thoughts."
On the inevitability of change: "The universe is change; our life is what our thoughts make it."
On the value of inner peace: "Nowhere can man find a quieter or more untroubled retreat than in his own soul."
On the importance of living in the present: "Do not act as if you were going to live ten thousand years. Death hangs over you. While you live, while it is in your power, be good."
